    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="78"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1"
                            >Generalissimo</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CKS1" type="to">Chiang</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d78fn1">Sent to the American Military Mission to China,
                        Chungking, via the White House Map Room and Army channels, as telegram 3734,
                        from the War Department to the Mission.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park</hi>
                        </placeName>?] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-30">30 October
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the President to <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CKS1">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>.</p>
                <p>I have not heard definitely from Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName> but there is still a chance of <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                        >Churchill</persName> and me meeting him near Persian Gulf.</p>
                <pb facs="0148" n="56" xml:id="pg_56"/>
                <p>Very confidentially, I hope you will make arrangements to meet with <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> and me in general neighborhood of
                    Cairo about November twenty-sixth.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Best regards</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
